JOHANNESBURG - One of the most anticipated comic book-to-big screen adaptations, Black Panther, finally has a release date: 16 February next year.The movie, from Marvel Studios, tells the back story of the original black super hero, T Challa, played by Chadwick Boseman (Gods of Egypt, Get on Up).Following the death of his father, the King of Wakanda, T'Challa returns home to the isolated, technologically-advanced African nation to take his rightful place as monarch.READ: Lupita Nyong'o excited for Black PantherBut, his mettle as king and that of his alter-ego, Black Panther, is tested when he is drawn into a conflict that puts the fate of his country and the entire world at risk. The character was introduced during a short cameo in last year's Captain America: Civil War and will become part of the ever-expanding Marvel universe. Black Panther also stars Michael B. Jordan as villain Erik Killmonger, Lupita Nyong o as the femme fatale Nakia, Martin Freeman as Everett K. Ross, as well as Angela Bassett and Forest Whitaker.The film is directed by Ryan Coogler (Creed), who also wrote the screenplay. eNCA